                    #steps-slider
                        //- Card 1
                        .ui.basic.card
                            .content
                                h2 Financial Identity Theft 
                                p Thieves use your personal information to open or use an account without your permission. 
                                    a(href='https://bjs.ojp.gov/topics/crime/identity-theft' target='_blank')
                                        sup [1]
                                    span  This may lead to:
                                .ui.bulleted.list
                                    .item Unexpected charges on statements or cards
                                    .item Unknown credit cards or loans in your name
                                    .item Surprise calls from debt collectors
                                    .item Denied credit or credit score drop
                                    .item Bounced checks with available funds
                                        a(href='https://www.aura.com/learn/signs-of-identity-theft#:~:text=Bounced%20checks%20(if%20you%20know%20you%20have%20available%20funds)&text=A%20bounced%20check%20could%20indicate,contact%20your%20bank%20right%20away.' target='_blank')
                                            sup [2]
                        //- Card 2 
                        .ui.basic.card
                            .content
                                h2 Medical Identity Theft 
                                p Thieves use your personal information to submit fraudulent claims to Medicare or other health insurers without your authorization. 
                                    a(href='https://oig.hhs.gov/fraud/consumer-alerts/medical-identity-theft/' target='_blank')
                                        sup [3]
                                    span  This may lead to:
                                .ui.bulleted.list
                                    .item Bill for services or medications you didn't get
                                    .item Report or call about a medical debt you don't owe
                                    .item Notice saying you reached your benefit limit
                                    .item Denied insurance coverage due to tampered medical records
                                        a(href='https://consumer.ftc.gov/articles/what-know-about-medical-identity-theft' target='_blank') 
                                            sup [4]
                        //- Card 3
                        .ui.basic.card
                            .content
                                h2 Tax Identity Theft 
                                p Thieves use your personal information to file a fake tax return to get a refund that belongs to you. 
                                    a(href='https://www.irs.gov/newsroom/taxpayer-guide-to-identity-theft' target='_blank')
                                        sup [5]
                                    span  This may lead to:
                                .ui.bulleted.list
                                    .item Unrequested mail/email with new account details
                                    .item IRS records show income from an unknown employer
                                    .item IRS letter for an unfiled tax return
                                    .item IRS notice claiming unexpected tax or actions against you
                                    .item E-file issue due to duplicate Social Security number
                                        a(href='https://www.irs.gov/newsroom/taxpayer-guide-to-identity-theft' target='_blank')
                                            sup [6]
